Ars&egrave;ne Wenger on how many players Arsenal will sign during the summer transfer window: <br />
<br />
- &quot;I would say three, maximum.&quot;

Wojciech Szczesny's agent has confirmed to Polish media &quot;there is still no agreement with Juventus&quot; following reports of a &pound;14m bid.<br />
<br />
Szczesny's agent, David Manasseh: &quot;Szczesny has yet to talk with Wenger, who has been confirmed as Arsenal coach for the next two years.&quot;

Olivier Giroud on his future: &quot;I am not insensitive to the approaches of the French clubs &amp; especially that of Marseille.&quot; [Telefoot] #afc<br />
<br />
Giroud: &quot;But my future is in the PL. I still have titles to win. After the FA Cup [win], we will go for the league title. That's my goal.&quot;

Leonardo Jardim:<br />
<br />
&ldquo;I think the project at Monaco is not yet finished. I will renew my contract, it will be made official soon.&rdquo;
